# VPS Hardening Guide (Ubuntu + Hetzner + Tailscale)

## Goal

This guide creates a hardened Ubuntu VPS with:

- SSH keys only
- No public SSH exposure
- Tailscale-only SSH access
- Non-root administration
- Firewall protection
- Fail2ban protection
- Reusable hardened VPS template

---

# Step 1 — Create VPS

Recommended:

- Ubuntu 24.04 LTS
- Hetzner Cloud
- Add SSH public key during server creation

Recommended specs:

## Basic VPS

- 2 vCPU
- 4 GB RAM
- 40–80 GB SSD

## Larger VPS

- 4–8 vCPU
- 8–16 GB RAM

---

# Step 2 — Login As Root

```bash
ssh root@SERVER_PUBLIC_IP
```

Update server:

```bash
apt update && apt upgrade -y
```

Optional reboot:

```bash
reboot
```

---

# Step 3 — Create Non-Root User

Replace `YOUR_USERNAME` with your username.

```bash
adduser YOUR_USERNAME
usermod -aG sudo YOUR_USERNAME
```

Verify sudo access:

```bash
id YOUR_USERNAME
```

Expected output should include:

```text
sudo
```

---

# Step 4 — Copy SSH Keys To User

```bash
mkdir -p /home/YOUR_USERNAME/.ssh
cp /root/.ssh/authorized_keys /home/YOUR_USERNAME/.ssh/
chown -R YOUR_USERNAME:YOUR_USERNAME /home/YOUR_USERNAME/.ssh
chmod 700 /home/YOUR_USERNAME/.ssh
chmod 600 /home/YOUR_USERNAME/.ssh/authorized_keys
```

---

# Step 5 — Verify SSH Key Authentication

From local machine:

```bash
ssh YOUR_USERNAME@SERVER_PUBLIC_IP
```

This MUST work without password prompt.

If it does not:

Check server authorized_keys:

```bash
cat ~/.ssh/authorized_keys
```

Expected format:

```text
ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3Nza... yourname@MacBook
```

---

# Step 6 — Install Tailscale

On VPS:

```bash
curl -fsSL https://tailscale.com/install.sh | sh
```

Authenticate:

```bash
sudo tailscale up
```

Open the login URL in browser.

---

# Step 7 — Get Tailscale IP

```bash
tailscale ip -4
```

Example:

```text
100.79.137.69
```

---

# Step 8 — Verify Tailscale SSH Access

From local machine:

```bash
ssh YOUR_USERNAME@TAILSCALE_IP
```

Example:

```bash
ssh presswhizz@100.79.137.69
```

This MUST work before continuing.

---

# Step 9 — Configure Firewall (UFW)

Install UFW if needed:

```bash
sudo apt install ufw -y
```

Configure firewall:

```bash
sudo ufw default deny incoming
sudo ufw default allow outgoing
sudo ufw allow in on tailscale0
sudo ufw allow 80/tcp
sudo ufw allow 443/tcp
sudo ufw enable
```

Verify:

```bash
sudo ufw status verbose
```

Expected:

```text
Anywhere on tailscale0 ALLOW IN
80/tcp ALLOW IN
443/tcp ALLOW IN
```

---

# Step 10 — Harden SSH Configuration

Edit SSH config:

```bash
sudo nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config
```

Find or add these lines:

```text
PermitRootLogin no
PasswordAuthentication no
PubkeyAuthentication yes
ChallengeResponseAuthentication no
UsePAM yes
X11Forwarding no
MaxAuthTries 3
ClientAliveInterval 300
ClientAliveCountMax 2
```

Save:

```text
CTRL + O
ENTER
CTRL + X
```

---

# Step 11 — Restrict SSH To Tailscale Only

Create socket override:

```bash
sudo mkdir -p /etc/systemd/system/ssh.socket.d
sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/ssh.socket.d/listen.conf
```

Paste:

```ini
[Socket]
ListenStream=
ListenStream=TAILSCALE_IP:22
```

Example:

```ini
[Socket]
ListenStream=
ListenStream=100.79.137.69:22
```

Reload SSH:

```bash
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl restart ssh.socket
sudo systemctl restart ssh
```

---

# Step 12 — Verify Hardened SSH

Open NEW terminal.

Verify Tailscale access still works:

```bash
ssh YOUR_USERNAME@TAILSCALE_IP
```

Verify public SSH is dead:

```bash
ssh YOUR_USERNAME@SERVER_PUBLIC_IP
```

Expected:

- Tailscale IP works
- Public IP hangs or refuses connection

This confirms SSH is no longer publicly exposed.

---

# Step 13 — Lock Root Account

```bash
sudo passwd -l root
```

This disables root password login.

---

# Step 14 — Install Fail2ban

Install:

```bash
sudo apt install fail2ban -y
```

Enable:

```bash
sudo systemctl enable fail2ban
sudo systemctl start fail2ban
```

Verify:

```bash
sudo fail2ban-client status
```

Expected:

```text
Jail list: sshd
```

---

# Step 15 — Recommended Hetzner Cloud Firewall

Allow:

```text
80
443
```

Do NOT allow:

```text
22
```

SSH should only work through Tailscale.

---

# Step 16 — VS Code Remote SSH Setup

Recommended SSH config:

```text
Host myserver
    HostName 100.79.137.69
    User YOUR_USERNAME
    IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_ed25519
```

Connect:

```bash
ssh myserver
```

Or use VS Code Remote SSH.

---

# Step 17 — Snapshot Strategy

After setup:

Create VPS snapshot.

Recommended name:

```text
ubuntu24-hardened-base
```

Benefits:

- reusable secure templates
- fast deployments
- disaster recovery
- consistent infrastructure

