# Security Principles

## Use Non-Root Users

Operate through:

```bash
sudo
```

Never daily-drive root.

---

## Use SSH Keys Only

Never enable password SSH authentication.

---

## Use Tailscale

Instead of:

```text
Public Internet → SSH Port 22
```

You get:

```text
Private Mesh Network → SSH
```

Massively reduced attack surface.

---

## Snapshot Frequently

Take snapshots before:

- upgrades
- Docker changes
- dependency experiments

---

# Common Problems

## Locked Out After Hardening

Usually caused by:

- wrong Tailscale IP
- forgetting to verify Tailscale SSH first
- incorrect socket binding

Fix:

- use Hetzner console
- revert ssh.socket override

---

## VS Code Remote SSH Fails

Usually caused by:

- using public IP instead of Tailscale IP
- local Tailscale disconnected

Verify:

```bash
tailscale status
```

---

## SSH Still Publicly Reachable

Check:

```bash
sudo ss -tulpn | grep :22
```

Only Tailscale IP should be listening.

